definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To inflict minor damage upon, especially by hitting or striking.
( transitive , colloquial ) To fire or reject .
examples: His top school dinged him last week.

definitions.definition: ( transitive , colloquial ) To deduct , as points, from (somebody), in the manner of a penalty; to penalize .
examples: My bank dinged me three bucks for using their competitor's ATM.

definitions.definition: ( transitive , golf ) To mishit (a golf ball).

definitions.definition: To make a high-pitched resonant sound like a bell.
To keep repeating; impress by reiteration, with reference to the monotonous striking of a bell.
